jQuery plugin that adds drawing HTML5 drawing capability to a webpage.  
Influenced by (http://mrdoob.com/projects/harmony/)

Include jQuery library and jsSketchPad.js to your page's HTML HEAD section.  
Create a containing element to hold and position your drawing area.

<div id="drawing_container"></div>

Call sketchyPad method on your arbitrary container element and sketchyPad will append canvas elements to the DOM.

jQuery("#drawing_container").sketchyPad({
//options
  width:600,
  height:600,
});

See sample.html for example implementation.

If you prefer another color picker, simply bind the onChange event to the setColor static function.

jQuery.sketchyPad.setColor(...);

Create custom brushes by adding your own brush file in brushes folder.  


